abstract: It has been over a month since any relevant state-level poll was conducted. So if candidates like Cory Booker or Tulsi Gabbard have made gains in early-voting states, there’s no polling to show it.

abstract: Everything you need to know about the 2020 Democratic presidential debate in Los Angeles.
snippet: Everything you need to know about the 2020 Democratic presidential debate in Los Angeles.
lead_paragraph: Only seven Democratic presidential candidates — the fewest yet — will take the stage at Loyola Marymount University on Thursday night, with 46 days to go until the first votes are cast in the Iowa caucuses. Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. remains the leading candidate in national polls, but three candidates are within striking distance, particularly in Iowa: Mayor Pete Buttigieg of South Bend, Ind., Senator Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts and Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont.

abstract: Fragments of pre-Aztec murals recently unearthed on the outskirts of what was once the largest city of the Americas are adding to mounting evidence that even commoners there enjoyed the finer things in life.

lead_paragraph: TEOTIHUACAN, Mexico — Fragments of pre-Aztec murals recently unearthed on the outskirts of what was once the largest city of the Americas are adding to mounting evidence that even commoners there enjoyed the finer things in life.
headline_main: Stylish Suburbs: How Ancient Mexican Metropolis Dodged Inequality Trap

lead_paragraph: LONDON — Stormzy didn’t have a moment to waste. He accelerated into a sharp left at a busy south London intersection as a traffic light flashed to red, sending the Ghanaian prayer beads dangling from the steering console of his Lamborghini flying. “Sorry, guys!” he said to his passengers with a grin.

headline_main: Can Stormzy, an Evangelist for British Grime, Seduce the U.S.?

abstract: Large in scope but small in size, the sonnet encapsulates infinitely malleable spirits within a finite frame, as we do.
snippet: Large in scope but small in size, the sonnet encapsulates infinitely malleable spirits within a finite frame, as we do.
lead_paragraph: When in distress with cancer and its treatments, I think of Shakespeare “in disgrace with fortune and men’s eyes” and all alone lament my downcast state. I am not completely bereft, then, because his poem supports my complaint. Why are sonnets so bracing, I wonder as I launch into a neo-Shakespearean sort of pity party.
